Description.val:
HC-130 recapitalization will replace and augment the aging USAF fleet of combat rescue HC-130P/N aircraft which are experiencing airworthiness, maintainability and operational limitations.  A common baseline aircraft configuration is being provided for the HC-130 Recap, the MC-130 Recap and the AC-130 Recap programs.  

Beginning with the FY11 President's Budget, the HC-130 Recap and MC-130 Recap programs are being reported separately for improved visibility.  
 
This program has associated Research Development Test and Evaluation (RDT&E) funding in PE 0605278F. 

Funding for this exhibit is contained in PE 0207224F.

Justification.val: The FY 2015 budget supports the production of 4 HC-130J and provides for logistics support.

Description.val:
HC-130 recapitalization will replace and augment the aging USAF fleets of combat rescue HC-130P/N aircraft which are experiencing airworthiness, maintainability and operational limitations.  A common baseline aircraft configuration is being provided for the HC-130 Recap, the MC-130 Recap and new AC-130 Recap programs.   

Beginning with the FY11 President's Budget, the HC-130 Recap and MC-130 Recap programs are being reported separately for improved visibility.  FY08-10 HC-130 Recap program details are reported as part of the HC/MC Recap program.

Advance procurement items are limited to components whose long-lead times
require purchase early in order to reduce the overall procurement lead-time
of the major end item.  These long lead items include structural components, engine mounts, engine components, flap shafts, and generators. 

Funding for this exhibit contained in PE 0207224F.

Justification.val: The FY15 budget supports advance procurement for 5 HC-130J aircraft and provides for logistics support.

Remarks.val:
The MC-130J, HC-130J, and AC-130J are managed as a common platform and PMA costs are shared. 

NOTE:  The FY13 aircraft quantity is 3 and the FY19 aircraft quantity is 1.  The FY13 and FY19 quantities on the P-40 are wrong but the funding is correct.

OverallDeliveryScheduleRemarks.val:
What appear to be gaps in production are filled by other USG C-130Js as well as foreign military sales and direct commercial sales aircraft.

See the C-130J P-21 for complete C-130J production plan, Line P-5.
